). Pair of ear-shaped lobes adjacent to both sides of dorsal base of cephalic veil. Buccal tentacles with wide longitudinal grooves, arising posterior to cephalic veil (
Figs 8A
; 
9A
).

Operculum semicircular; dorsal and lateral margin well developed, with 26 – 32 ( holotype 29) triangular lappets; ventral margin (opercular ridge) with 11 – 13 ( holotype with 12 left, 13 right) pairs of golden paleae, curved dorsally, acute with extended tips (
Figs 8A – C
;
9A – B
).

First pair of tentacular cirri extending to tips of paleae, with annuli, arising from connection of opercular margin and paleal ridge (

